        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  don't know why changing cw is more intrusive than Y.\r\n\r\nbecause it's a way more common operation that almost every vi-emulation also supports - and they match the existing behaviour.\r\nAnd one also has to consider the intent of the user.  If you delete a word you usually don't want to leave an extra whitespace in the line. If you change a word you are likely to keep the whitespace.\r\nConsistency as argument is decent as tie breaker if there are no other compelling arguments, but as a standalone argument it's pretty weak\r\n\r\n",
